oc:kn_29687997 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any cancel flow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use dark patterns — hiding cancel buttons, adding excessive steps, or making 'continue cancelling' hard to find damages brand trust and may violate FTC Click-to-Cancel rules." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dark patterns breed resentment, generate bad reviews, and violate regulations in many jurisdictions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_55d01c30 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building cancel flows from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every cancel flow should follow: Trigger → Exit Survey → Dynamic Save Offer → Confirmation → Post-Cancel. One primary offer + one fallback per reason, never a wall of options." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This sequence captures intent, enables personalized retention, respects the customer's choice, and leaves the door open" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5bb6c332 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing discount save offers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid discounts exceeding 30%. Deep discounts (50%+) train customers to cancel-and-return for deals, devaluing the product long-term." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Customers who learn they can get deep discounts by threatening to cancel become repeat discount-seekers, eroding revenue" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_619cb41e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, before generating any churn prevention recommendations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting, check for product marketing context at .agents/product-marketing-context.md or .claude/product-marketing-context.md. Gather: monthly churn rate, subscriber count, average MRR, billing provider, billing intervals, usage tracking capabilities, B2B/B2C, brand tone." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Context-aware recommendations are dramatically more actionable than generic advice" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_709a3292 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When diagnosing overall churn situation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Voluntary churn is typically 50-70% of total churn; involuntary (failed payments) is 30-50% but is often easier to fix. Address both types." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Many teams focus only on voluntary churn and miss the easily recoverable involuntary churn from payment failures" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_785eef84 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When offering pause subscription as a save option" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Limit subscription pauses to 1-3 months maximum. Pauses beyond 3 months rarely reactivate. Allow at most 1 pause per 12-month period." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Extended pauses decay relationship with the product; short pauses with auto-reactivation preserve the customer relationship" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ab0fc147 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When measuring cancel flow effectiveness" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A 'saved' customer who churns 30 days later wasn't really saved. Track save offer LTV, not just save rate, to measure genuine retention." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Save rate alone is a vanity metric — genuine retention requires the customer to stay and remain engaged long-term" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b1bebfdf a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building proactive retention systems" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Build a health score (0-100) from weighted signals: login frequency × 0.30, feature usage × 0.25, support sentiment × 0.15, billing health × 0.15, engagement × 0.15. Score 80-100 = healthy, 60-79 = needs attention, 40-59 = at risk, 0-39 = critical." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A weighted composite score enables automated risk-tiered interventions before customers reach the cancel button" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b7eb5be2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing exit surveys" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use exit survey with 5-8 single-select reason options (too expensive, not using enough, missing feature, switching to competitor, technical issues, temporary/seasonal, business closed, other with free text). Use 'Help us improve' framing, not 'Why are you leaving?'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Proper framing and right number of options maximizes response quality without causing decision fatigue" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e27314c2 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When mapping save offers to exit survey reasons" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match the save offer to the cancel reason. A discount won't save someone who isn't using the product; a feature roadmap won't save someone who can't afford it." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mismatched offers waste the cancel flow opportunity — the offer must address the actual reason for cancellation" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

